LST-PREG-project

## Overview
This repository contains GWAS and Mendelian Randomization (MR) code for a study investigating the causal relationship between leisure screen time (LST) and risks of pregnancy-related health disorders, including ectopic pregnancy, miscarriages, polycystic ovarian syndrome (PCOS), and endometriosis. Key findings include:
- 25 female-specific SNPs and 9 male-specific SNPs were identified in our sex-stratified GWAS. 
- LST exhibits higher heritability in females compared to males.
- Female-specific genetic instruments reveal that higher LST increases risks of ectopic pregnancy , PCOS , and endometriosis .
- LST exceeding 2 hours/day significantly elevates ectopic pregnancy risk, with further escalation beyond 6 hours/day.

---

## Installation
